    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A thematic, dashboard-style SPA designed to guide the user through Localiza's financial story. The structure is non-linear compared to the report, starting with a high-level overview, then diving into thematic sections: 1) Growth Engine (DRE), 2) Capital Structure (Balance Sheet), 3) The Cash Conundrum (Cash Flow Anomaly), 4) Risk Dashboard, and 5) Strategic Core (Business Model). This narrative approach was chosen to make the complex financial data more digestible and to highlight the key findings (like the cash flow anomaly) more effectively for better user understanding and engagement. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: DRE Trends -> Bar/Line Chart (Goal: Compare/Change, shows scale difference between Revenue and Profit). Revenue Split -> Donut Chart (Goal: Compare Proportion). Asset Growth -> Stacked Area Chart (Goal: Change/Compare, visually represents the capital-intensive model and merger impact). Cash Flow Anomaly -> Bar Chart with negative values (Goal: Highlight Anomaly, clearly contrasts negative operating cash with positive financing cash). Risk Ratios -> Line Chart (Goal: Show Change over time). Business Model -> HTML/CSS Diagram (Goal: Organize/Explain Process, avoids SVG/Mermaid). All choices use Chart.js on Canvas for interactivity and responsiveness, adhering to the no-SVG constraint. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
